cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new obfuscation technique for a communication protocol to make reverse engineering more complex. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper presents the design of a framework that implements the proposed obfuscation technique by automatically generating a library performing the corresponding transformations. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the obfuscation transformations are applied to the Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) representation of the messages. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is possible as the paper discusses the practical deployment of the approach in operation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of various metrics recorded from experiments to show the increase in complexity of the obfuscated protocol binary.
